1276	/// First half of `luaK_posfix`: pre-process the left operand `v` of a binary
1277	/// operator before the right operand is parsed. Mirrors C's `luaK_infix`
1278	/// from `lcode.c`. The codegen reconciliation has not yet routed parser
1279	/// calls through `lua_code::infix`, so this lives in the parser file
1280	/// alongside the other `cg_*` helpers.
1281	///
1282	/// For `And`/`Or` the operand is converted into a short-circuit form (jump
1283	/// list closed via `cg_go_if_true` / `cg_go_if_false`). For `Concat` it is
1284	/// pushed onto the next register. Other arithmetic, bitwise, and comparison
